CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18, reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley...Center photo shows Rev. and Mrs. Talley after the banquet well pleased with the reception they received...Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Rev. Cornell E. Talley posed in front of ferns for banquet in his honor in Central Baptist Church decorated with fringe and crepe paper streamers
